commitResults.messageTitle: Implement Customer class, AddCustomerCommand, and AddCustomerCommandParser
commitResults.messageBody:
- Add the `Customer` class, extending from `Person`, with additional fields:
  - `openCustomerOrders`: to store a list of unfulfilled customer orders.
  - `information`: for storing additional customer-specific details.

- Implement `AddCustomerCommand` to handle adding customers to the address book.
  - Handles execution logic for creating and adding a customer.

- Implement `AddCustomerCommandParser` to parse CLI input for adding customers.
  - Parses fields such as name, phone, email, address, dietary preference, information, and optional tags.

- Update CLI logic to support the `add customer` command.
  - Command format: `add customer n/NAME p/PHONE e/EMAIL a/ADDRESS pref/PREFERENCE i/INFORMATION [t/TAG]...`
  - Example usage: `add customer n/Emily Tan p/81234567 e/emily@example.com a/456 Cupcake Road pref/No gluten i/Allergic to nuts t/loyal`

- Added error handling and logging to track and fix potential issues during command execution.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Supplier feature with CLI parsing support
commitResults.messageBody:
- Implement Supplier class to represent suppliers in the address book
  - Includes fields for name, phone, email, address, dietary preference, ingredients supplied, and tags
  - Add methods for managing open supply orders and ingredients supplied

- Add AddSupplierCommand class to handle the addition of suppliers
  - Executes the logic for adding a new supplier to the address book
  - Includes necessary validation and duplicate supplier checks

- Implement AddSupplierCommandParser class to parse supplier addition commands from the CLI
  - Parses input fields like name, phone, email, address, preference, and ingredients supplied
  - Uses the new IngredientsParser method to parse ingredients supplied into a structured data type

- Refactore the logic for parsing ingredients supplied in ParserUtil
  - Create parseIngredients method to handle the parsing of ingredients supplied from a comma-separated string input

commitResults.messageBody:
- Modify `Customer` class to include a "customer" tag automatically for all customer entries for easy identification
- Update `PersonCard` class to apply custom styles for the "customer" tag.
- Update `AddCustomerCommandParser` to ensure that the customer tag is correctly assigned during customer creation.
- Add CSS rules in `DarkTheme.css` to style the "customer" tag with a red background and white text.
- Ensure that the custom customer tag is displayed in the GUI with the intended red color for improved visual distinction.

- Modifiy the `AddSupplierCommandParser` class to automatically add a "supplier" tag when a supplier is created.
- Updated the `PersonCard` class to apply the custom "tag-supplier" CSS class to the "supplier" tag.
- Add new styles in `DarkTheme.css` to style the "supplier" tag with a green background.
- Ensure that the "supplier" tag is now displayed with a green color for better visual distinction from other tags.
